## Conventions

- Keep section structure stable: hero, services, gallery, service area, and contact.
- Keep **accessibility**: skip link, nav `aria-*`, meaningful `alt` on images, descriptive `title` on the map iframe.
- Hero background image lives in CSS; if changing hero photography, update both [`index.html`](index.html) and [`src/style.css`](src/style.css) where needed.
- Placeholder imagery is acceptable until real project photos are available.

## Mobile

- The site must **work well on mobile**: test layouts at narrow widths (e.g. <=390px), keep tap targets adequate (`--tap-min`), and ensure the mobile nav, grids, and embeds do not overflow horizontally.
- Keep CTA buttons highly visible in mobile hero.
- Gallery “compact” mode and mobile nav breakpoint behavior should stay aligned with existing CSS breakpoints unless intentionally changed.

## Keep this rule in sync

When you change **deploy base path**, **contact/location details**, **brand name**, **documented stack**, or **project conventions**, **update this `.mdc` file in the same change** so it stays accurate for future sessions.
